gomodel:SYNGO_5176  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3: Smaug1 (SAMD4A) localized to postsynapses in hippocampal neurons .\n\nFigure 9: confocal imaging of hippocampal neurons subjected to siRNA knockdown of Smaug1 (SAMD4A) showed reduced synapse size and number.\n\n\"We found that both PSD95 and synapsin clusters were smaller and more numerous than in control or siNT-treated cells (Fig. 9 C and not depicted).\n...\nPSD95-containing synapses in hippocampal cells are mostly excitatory, and are located in dendritic spines. To visualize dendritic spines, neurons were transfected with ECFP and stained for PSD95 (Fig. 9 F). As expected, PSD95 clusters were located at the tip of dendritic spines. Remarkably, dendritic spines were longer and thinner in siSmaug1-treated cells, thus resembling an immature morphology.\". Experimental description: M&M:\n\"Hippocampal cultures were prepared as described previously (Banker and Goslin, 1998). In brief, hippocampi were dissected from Sprague Dawley rats at embryonic day 18 and digested with trypsin.\"\n\nsiRNA treatment:\n\"Either a pool against rat Smaug1 (catalog no. M-086491-00-0010) containing the sequences 5'-AAUAUAAGCUCCUAUCUAC-3' (siSmaug1a), 5'-GACCGGACCUCCACAAUCU-3' (siSmaug1b), 5'-UGGCAGAACUCUCGGGAUU-3' (siSmaug1c), and 5'-ACGCGAAAGUAGAGUAUAU-3' (siSmaug1d) at 25 nM each or the individual sequences at 100 nM were used. A pool of four sequences against rat Smaug2 (siSmaug2, catalog no. M-081919-00) and an siCONTROL nontargeting pool (D-001810-10; Thermo Fisher Scientific) were used at 100 nM.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-26" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5176" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

